The rocket attack on the US embassy in Athens has reignited fears of extreme left-wing violence in Greece.
The country's security forces have intensified surveillance efforts following the dismantling of November 17 and ELA before the Athens 2004 Olympics.
Despite the break-up of these radical groups, the recent attack underscores the persistent threat.
Italian Foreign Minister condemned the attack and expressed solidarity with the US.
Greek authorities are investigating the involvement of the extreme left-wing group Revolutionary Struggle.
US and Greek authorities are collaborating to identify and prosecute those responsible, emphasizing the seriousness of such violent acts.
